<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> He pauses.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Crushbone. Now there's a hive of creatures I have not hunted. I remember my first journey to Faydwer well; I was rather young when I made it, but my seasons there were not spent in the Faydark, but rather in the mountains of Butcherblock with a druidic friend of mine who has long since departed this world. A shame we did not meet then...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Keats grins roguishly.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
...both our stories might have been very different.<br>
